        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 5 at 11:14PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1114 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Bowbells, or 36 miles north of Stanley, moving northeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bowbells, Sherwood, Flaxton, Niobe, Coteau, and Northgate.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
